# 
tf.keras.backend.clear_session()

# CNNSequential
cnn_model = models.Sequential([
    layers.Input(shape=(32, 32, 3)), # CIFAR-1032323 RGB

    # 1+
    layers.Conv2D(
        filters=32,          # 32
        kernel_size=(3, 3),  # 33
        activation='relu',   # ReLU
        padding='same',      #  SAME32323232
    ),
    layers.MaxPooling2D(
        pool_size=(2, 2),    # 2232321616
        strides=(2, 2)       # =2
    ),
    
    # 2
    layers.Conv2D(
        filters=64,          # 
        kernel_size=(3, 3),
        activation='relu',
        padding='same'
    ),
    layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2), strides=(2, 2)),  # 161688
    
    # 3
    layers.Conv2D(
        filters=128,         # 
        kernel_size=(3, 3),
        activation='relu',
        padding='same'
    ),
    layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2), strides=(2, 2)),  # 8844
    
    # 44128
    layers.Flatten(),  # 44128 = 2048
    
    # 12048256
    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dropout(0.5),  # Dropout50%
    
    # 10CIFAR-1010
    layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')  # softmax1
])

# 
print("CNN")
cnn_model.summary()  #

# +
def show_predict_examples(num_examples=10):
    # num_examples
    random_idx = np.random.choice(len(x_test_processed), num_examples, replace=False)
    sample_x = x_test_processed[random_idx]
    sample_y_true = y_test_flat[random_idx]
    sample_y_pred = y_pred[random_idx]
    
    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 3))
    for i in range(num_examples):
        plt.subplot(1, num_examples, i+1)
        plt.xticks([])
        plt.yticks([])
        plt.grid(False)
        
        # 
        plt.imshow(sample_x[i])
        
        # 
        if sample_y_true[i] == sample_y_pred[i]:
            color = 'green'
            status = ''
        else:
            color = 'red'
            status = ''
        
        # +
        true_label = class_names[sample_y_true[i]]
        pred_label = class_names[sample_y_pred[i]]
        plt.xlabel(f"{true_label}\n{pred_label}", color=color, fontsize=8)
    
    plt.suptitle(f'CNN==', fontsize=12)
    plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.9]) 
    plt.show()

# 
show_predict_examples(num_examples=10)

def show_vehicle_error_examples(num_examples=5):
    # 
    vehicle_error_mask = (vehicle_y_true != vehicle_y_pred)  # /
    error_count = np.sum(vehicle_error_mask)
    
    if np.sum(vehicle_error_mask) == 0:
        print("")
        return
    
    error_idx = np.where(vehicle_error_mask)[0][:num_examples]  # num_examples
    sample_x = vehicle_x_test[error_idx]
    sample_y_true = vehicle_y_true[error_idx]
    sample_y_pred = vehicle_y_pred[error_idx]
    
    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 3))
    for i in range(len(error_idx)):
        plt.subplot(1, len(error_idx), i+1)
        plt.xticks([])
        plt.yticks([])
        plt.grid(False)
        
        # 
        plt.imshow(sample_x[i])
        
        # +
        true_label = class_names[sample_y_true[i]]
        pred_label = class_names[sample_y_pred[i]]
        plt.xlabel(f"{true_label}\n{pred_label}", color='red', fontsize=10)
    
    plt.suptitle(f'', fontsize=12)
    plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.9])
    plt.show()
